summary: This is a calendar entry for a 30-minute 'Update Conference Call' scheduled for August 13, 2019, involving multiple U.S. government agencies including the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS), the Office of the Inspector General (OIG), and the FBI. The call appears to be an internal coordination meeting related to the Epstein case.

events.title: Update Conference Call
events.description: A scheduled 30-minute conference call organized by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS), with attendees from OIG, OGA, and FBI offices in New York.

keyFacts: A multi-agency conference call was scheduled for August 13, 2019, to discuss updates on the Epstein case.
The call was organized by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS).
Attendees included representatives from the Office of the Inspector General (OIG), another government agency (OGA), and the FBI's New York office.
The calendar entry was created and modified on August 13, 2019, just hours before the scheduled call.
The call was marked with high priority (Priority: 5) and had a reminder alarm set for 15 minutes before the start time.
